Facial Appearanace Experiment Data

Contains data from an experiment using competence measures (self-reported based on brief exposure to image of a candidate's face) to predict election outcomes.

face

Format

A data frame with 119 rows and 10 variables:

year
integer: year of the election
state
character: state of the election
winner
character: name of the winner
loser
character: name of the runner-up
w.party
character: party of the winner
l.party
character: party of the loser
d.comp
numeric: competence measure for the Democratic candidate
r.comp
numeric: competence measure for the Republican candidate
d.votes
integer: number of votes for the Democratic candidate
r.votes
integer: number of votes for the Republican candidate

Details

See QSS Table 4.4.

References

  • Imai, Kosuke. 2017. Quantitative Social Science: An Introduction. Princeton University Press. http://press.princeton.edu/titles/11025.html.
